		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />When you set a breakpoint, you may want it to trigger only when a particular page is mapped into memory at that address.
<br />You also need to consider whether the memory is ROM or not, and if the memory is bankswitchable.  If you're hacking some hypothetical game that has bankswitchable SRAM and stores code there, you'd need to be able to have the breakpoint target the correct memory.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


