	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">But NES CPU addresses are 16bit long, not 24... ^_^;; 0000-FFFF</div>
<br />...which is why bankswitching exists in the first place. He's proposing the 24-bit breakpoints exactly because different banks can be mapped to the same addressable space (not at the same time), but you most likely only want a breakpoint for one of them. Breakpoint addresses accompanied by a bank number, or NES file breakpoints would allow that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


